# Commit And Push Project Work

When the user asks for completed project changes to be committed/pushed, do not stop at local edits.

- Run focused validation and any required build, artifact, or deployment update steps.
- Commit the completed changes with a clear message once validation passes.
- Push the commit to the requested branch/remote when the user explicitly asks for push, says the work is incomplete unless pushed, or asks to complete a fix for this project.
- If a pushed install/test artifact is needed for reinstall visibility, rebuild/update it before committing.
- Never claim changes are complete when required commits, pushes, artifacts, manifests, or deployments are still pending.
